OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHouseholds already in debt 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fas energy bills rise       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Many households are falling behind on  
OL,6, energy payments with total debt owed   
OL,7, three times higher than in September   
OL,8, last year, a survey has suggested.     
OL,10,FAlmost a quarter of households owe #206
OL,11,Fon average, according to comparison    
OL,12,Fsite Uswitch, which surveyed 2,000.    
OL,14,FUswitch advised people falling into    
OL,15,Fdebt to speak to their provider to work
OL,16,Fout a more affordable payment plan.    
OL,18,FThe data comes as consultancy Cornwall 
OL,19,FInsight warned energy bills could rise 
OL,20,Fmuch higher than thought in October.   
